In [10]:
# Replace null values in Embark with mode.

5. Outlier Detection¶

In [20]:
sns.boxplot(df["Fare"])
Out[20]:
<Axes: >
In [21]:
df['Age'].skew()
Out[21]:
0.4344880940129925
In [22]:
df['Fare'].skew() #Skew is larger than 1
Out[22]:
4.787316519674893

There are outliers in Fare.

Hence we perform flooring and capping

In [23]:
q1 = df.Fare.quantile(0.25)
q3 = df.Fare.quantile(0.75)
In [24]:
IQR =q3-q1
In [25]:
upper_limit =q3+1.5*IQR
In [26]:
lower_limit =q3-1.5*IQR
In [27]:
df['Fare']=np.where(df['Fare']>upper_limit,upper_limit,np.where(df['Fare']<lower_limit,lower_limit,df['Fare']))
In [28]:
sns.boxplot(df["Fare"])
Out[28]:
<Axes: >
